OL,3,CMontgomeryshire & Glyndwr: How the
OL,4,Ctide turned for the typically Tory seat
OL,6,FIn 2019, Craig Williams won the seat
OL,7,Ffor the Conservatives by a 12,138
OL,8,Fmajority having received 20,020 votes.
OL,9,FLiberal Democrat Kishan Devani was
OL,10,Fsecond with 7,882 votes and Labour's
OL,11,FKait Duerden third with 5,585 votes.
OL,13,FThis year's General Election result
OL,14,Fpainted a very different picture. The
OL,15,Fnew constituency of Montgomeryshire &
OL,16,FGlyndwr saw Labour's Steve Witherden
OL,17,Fobtain 12,709 votes, followed by
OL,18,FReform UK's Oliver Lewis at 8,894
OL,19,Fvotes.
