OL,3,CMontgomeryshire & Glyndwr: How the
OL,4,Ctide turned for the typically Tory seat
OL,6,FShe said: "People have voted Labour
OL,7,Fnot necessarily because they have any
OL,8,Ffaith in Labour at all, it's just the
OL,9,Fembarrassment and shame that he (Craig
OL,10,FWilliams) could do such a thing.
OL,12,F"It was a back-up plan, not a
OL,13,Fconfident one, but if he hadn't done
OL,14,Fwhat he'd done, I'm sure we'd still be
OL,15,FConservative now."
OL,17,FRob Smith, a skipper for charity the
OL,18,FHeulwen Trust disagreed.
