OL,6,FHe said: "The majority of people took
OL,7,Fit quite lightly. We all make
OL,8,Fmistakes. And I know he does bitterly
OL,9,Fregret it. But I wouldn't have thought
OL,10,Fthat would have affected people voting
OL,11,Flocally."
OL,13,FA desire for change was at the heart
OL,14,Fof many locals' reasoning for
OL,15,Fswitching their votes.
OL,17,FMr Smith was a longstanding
OL,18,FConservative voter but it changed this
OL,19,Fyear.
